<item>
            <title>[LU-1804] Failure sanity-scrub test_9: Unexpected speed 182, should not less than 220</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1804</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/9bc93c26-f262-11e1-9def-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/9bc93c26-f262-11e1-9def-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_9 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(11) Unexpected speed 182, should not less than 220&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is probably due to running in a VM environment, where the whole VM may face CPU/memory/disk contention from other VMs running on the same node.  It may be that this test should have a lower threshold when running in a VM?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: sanity-scrub 9&lt;/p&gt;</description>
