                            <comment id="44086" author="yong.fan" created="Sun, 2 Sep 2012 23:08:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,3846&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,3846&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="44084" author="yong.fan" created="Sun, 2 Sep 2012 22:15:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The Maloo test log seems lost.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The OI scrub speed depends on the CPU/RAM schedule, there may be more delay under VM environment. But it is difficult to say which threshold is suitable. So may be we should skip speed related test under VM environment, but it is difficult for the test scripts to detect whether it is tested under VM environment or not. Another possible replacement is that skip OI scrub speed tests under the environment which has less CPU cores or hyper-threads. How do you think?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
